---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Glossary">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold mb-8 text-slate-900">Glossary</h1>
  <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">
    Searchable terminology reference for oligopeptide biology, chemistry, and pharmacology.
  </p>

  <div class="mb-6" id="search"></div>

  <div class="space-y-8">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-[#0D9488] border-b border-slate-200 pb-2">A</h2>
      <dl class="space-y-3">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-100">
          <dt class="font-bold text-slate-900">Amino Acid</dt>
          <dd class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">
            Organic molecule with both amino (−NH₂) and carboxyl (−COOH) groups. 20 standard amino
            acids are protein building blocks. Classified by side chain properties: hydrophobic,
            polar, charged.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-100">
          <dt class="font-bold text-slate-900">Antimicrobial Peptide (AMP)</dt>
          <dd class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">
            Short peptides (5-50 aa) that kill microorganisms. Part of innate immunity. Examples:
            defensins, cathelicidins, magainins. Mechanism: membrane disruption.
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-[#0D9488] border-b border-slate-200 pb-2">P</h2>
      <dl class="space-y-3">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-100">
          <dt class="font-bold text-slate-900">Peptide Bond</dt>
          <dd class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">
            Amide bond between amino acids. Formed by dehydration synthesis. Has partial double-bond
            character (resonance). Planar geometry. Typically trans configuration.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-100">
          <dt class="font-bold text-slate-900">Pharmacokinetics</dt>
          <dd class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">
            Study of ADME: Absorption, Distribution, Metabolism, Excretion. Key parameters:
            half-life (t½), bioavailability (F), clearance (CL), volume of distribution (Vd).
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-[#0D9488] border-b border-slate-200 pb-2">S</h2>
      <dl class="space-y-3">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-100">
          <dt class="font-bold text-slate-900">Spaced Repetition</dt>
          <dd class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">
            Learning technique with increasing intervals between reviews. Optimizes long-term
            retention. FSRS algorithm adapts intervals to individual learning patterns.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-100">
          <dt class="font-bold text-slate-900">Structure-Activity Relationship (SAR)</dt>
          <dd class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">
            Relationship between chemical structure and biological activity. Used in drug design to
            optimize potency, selectivity, and pharmacokinetics.
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
